helpdesk-ticket.description-html: User called asking how to change mouse pointer sensitivity

helpdesk-note.body: checked ID via address
helpdesk-note.body-html: checked ID via address

helpdesk-note.body: user requests instructions emailed, emailing and resolving
helpdesk-note.body-html: user requests instructions emailed, emailing and resolving

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi schenstr, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8707
The steps to change the mouse sensitivity are listed below, and I will be marking this issue resolved. However, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any additional feedback you would be willing to provide would be appreciated.
1) Select the Windows button in the bottom left 2) Search for and select "Mouse" 3) In the window that pops up select the pointer options tab 4) There is a drag bar labeled select pointer speed, which controls the sensitivity
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi schenstr,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8707

The steps to change the mouse sensitivity are listed below, and I will be marking this issue resolved. However, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any additional feedback you would be willing to provide would be appreciated.

1) Select the Windows button in the bottom left
2) Search for and select "Mouse"
3) In the window that pops up select the pointer options tab
4) There is a drag bar labeled select pointer speed, which controls the sensitivity

Thanks,
Thomas Schleich
helpdesk@msoe.edu
414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Follow You printer queue
helpdesk-ticket.description:
It seems to me that sometimes I submit jobs to the follow you print queue and I go to print them later, sometimes the next day, and they are not there. Does that print queue get cleaned out/purged occasionally/regularly that would cause this to happen? If not, other explanation? Thanks.
Mitch Colton
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
It seems to me that sometimes I submit jobs to the follow you print queue and I go to print them later, sometimes the next day, and they are not there.  Does that print queue get cleaned out/purged occasionally/regularly that would cause this to happen?  If not, other explanation?  Thanks.
 
Mitch Colton

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mitch Colton, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8731
Documents are cleared form the queue 24 hours after they were submitted. Thus, if you send something to the printer and then show up the next day, there is a very real possibility the print jobs will have expired. I will be marking this as resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns. Any feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: RE: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I will not be able to participate during the slotted time frame. Would it be possible to accommodate me after work hours (after 5 pm) or would it be ok for a family member to bring in the computer and have the audit and process completed with them. If so, please let me know what he/she would need to bring.
Also, where is IT located now? And approximately how long will the process take to complete?
Thank you very much, Timothy Schultz
From: Helpdesk Sent: Friday, May 27, 2016 2:21 PM Subject: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
[cid:image001.png@01D1BF55.65C093E0]
Congratulations!
My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.
As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th. Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed. If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner. Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma.
Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done. Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining. The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop.
Again congratulations on your accomplishment and we wish you much success as you leave the halls of MSOE and move onto to other opportunities.
MSOE Technology Program
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
MSOE IT Helpdesk (414)277-7288 helpdesk.msoe.edu
CC Great Room
Helpdesk Summer Hours Mon-Fri: 8:00a-4:30p

All,
See below, if it is convenient for you the IT department asks that faculty turn in their existing laptop by June 15th. The new laptops do not come in until August, so you would be given a loaner unit (current freshman G2 laptop) to use for 6 weeks. If it is too much of a hassle, just keep your old unit until August. But if you can please consider doing the swap, it does help save the university a little $.
Thanks,
Blake E. Wentz, PhD, CPC LEED (R) Accredited Professional Professor & Department Chair Civil, Architectural Engineering & Construction Management Department Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 N Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 wentz@msoe.edu<mailto:wentz@msoe.edu> Office - 414–277-2204
From: "Thomas, Richard" <thomasrh@msoe.edu<mailto:thomasrh@msoe.edu>> Date: Thursday, May 26, 2016 at 2:21 PM To: "Barnicki, Dr. Cynthia" <barnickc@msoe.edu<mailto:barnickc@msoe.edu>>, Blake Wentz <wentz@msoe.edu<mailto:wentz@msoe.edu>> Cc: "Harris, Benjamin" <harrisbj@msoe.edu<mailto:harrisbj@msoe.edu>>, "Bialek, Dr. Steven" <bialek@msoe.edu<mailto:bialek@msoe.edu>> Subject: RE: Dates for Lap Top Swap for ME department
For departments getting new laptops (not tablets). Those that need to hang onto their laptop can do so until August. We can extend those units at a penalty to MSOE, but it will remove the need to transition to a secondary unit.
If the faculty member does not need the laptop over the summer or can transition to the G2’s and can turn them in by June 15th. That would be exceptional, and would save the university a lot of money, until the new units are ready for deployment. (which will likely be in July)
We are trying not to inconvenience everyone and appreciate the effort of the faculty, so if they can transition to the G2’s that would be the most economical way to move forward. However, if that is a point of extreme frustration we have a separate way to move forward.
Hopefully this answers your questions, please let me know if I missed anything,
Thanks,
Rick Thomas Senior Director of IT Milwaukee School of Engineering 414.277.2350 www.msoe.edu<http://www.msoe.edu>
[MSOE-U-BK_RD.tif]

Rick,
I am just checking to see if there is updated information on the dates (and procedures) for the full-time faculty in the ME department to swap from our existing computers to the new G3 computers.
Steve Bialek mentioned the June 15th deadline for turning in the current computers (and then getting a G2 loaner) and then swapping the G2 loaner for the G3 computer in July may not be the current plan. I did ask the faculty to hold off either getting the G2, or if they had already picked one up to not spend a lot of time getting it functional. Many faculty are finishing grading and may be gone starting June 1st. I believe Steve indicated you would be sending an e-mail with the exact details of the swap this week.
I recognize that there are many challenges for you, and I very much appreciate Ben coming to the ME department meeting. It will be much easier to coordinate with many faculty this week, so time is critical in my view. I also appreciate your willingness to work with Vince Prantil on his issue.
Please let me know if I can do anything to help.
Cindy

For departments getting new laptops (not tablets). Those that need to hang onto their laptop can do so until August. We can extend those units at a penalty to MSOE, but it will remove the need to transition to a secondary unit.
 
If the faculty member does not need the laptop over the summer or can transition to the G2’s and can turn them in by June 15th. That would be exceptional, and would save the university a lot of money, until the new units are ready for deployment. (which will likely be in July)
 
We are trying not to inconvenience everyone and appreciate the effort of the faculty, so if they can transition to the G2’s that would be the most economical way to move forward. However, if that is a point of extreme frustration we have a separate way to move forward.

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
My work schedule will not allow me to bring my laptop to the Helpdesk during any of the summer hours. Is it possible for me to bring it any day after 5pm or before 7am? My laptop no longer has any MSOE software currently installed on it, so it hopefully will not take long.
Thanks,
Orion Schemenauer
On May 27, 2016, at 2:21 PM, Helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu<mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu>> wrote:
<image003.png>
Congratulations!
My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.
As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th. Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed. If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner. Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma.
Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done. Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining. The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop.
Again congratulations on your accomplishment and we wish you much success as you leave the halls of MSOE and move onto to other opportunities.
MSOE Technology Program
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
MSOE IT Helpdesk (414)277-7288 helpdesk.msoe.edu<http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/> CC Great Room
Helpdesk Summer Hours Mon-Fri: 8:00a-4:30p

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi schemenauero, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8818
Unfortunately we do not have the ability to receive a laptop outside of our regular work hours. However, we understand that this may be an inconvenience, and so if you provide us with explicit permission for someone to bring your laptop in and pick it up again, we are happy to allow them to do so. Note that if all of our software has been removed, we just need to look through the machine to confirm this, as well as that it is no longer our operating system. This means that if you would prefer to keep it the we would need access to your account on the machine when it was brought in. I will be marking this as resolved, however, please feel free to contact us with any additional questions or concerns.
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Brandy Peterson, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8830
Could you please try the following steps to ensure that your MSOE Community account is linked to your MSOE email address?
1) Navigate to https://www.msoe.edu/switcher_app/
2) Select "Switch From Personal Login" 3) Select "Switch To MSOE Email" 4) Login to the Community Site with your Personal Credentials 5) Fill out the information, and it should migrate your Community account to be linked to your MSOE email address
Once this has been completed, please try logging into community.msoe.edu with your MSOE credentials, and then accessing the financial aid site.
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

Could you please try the following steps to ensure that your MSOE Community account is linked to your MSOE email address?

1) Navigate to https://www.msoe.edu/switcher_app/
2) Select "Switch From Personal Login"
3) Select "Switch To MSOE Email"
4) Login to the Community Site with your Personal Credentials
5) Fill out the information, and it should migrate your Community account to be linked to your MSOE email address

Once this has been completed, please try logging into community.msoe.edu with your MSOE credentials, and then accessing the financial aid site.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: FW: Library color printer printing more than requested
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I checked Sarah’s Raider account. Gold only took off $.90 which would be for the 3 copies. But she received 9 copies. There must be something on the print side causing the extra copies. It happens to more people that just Sarah.
Sheila Barber Campus Card Administrator Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 N Broadway CC435 Milwaukee WI 53202 Work: (414) 277-7460
[cid:image001.png@01D1C169.826EA070] From: Rowell, Sarah Sent: Wednesday, June 08, 2016 9:32 AM To: Helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu>; Barber, Sheila <barber@msoe.edu> Subject: Library color printer printing more than requested
Good morning,
I just tried printing out 3 copies of a schedule in color and I got 9 instead. I know this has happened to other students in the past. Have you figured out what triggers this so we can fix it or at least warn/redirect students as to what to do to avoid it?
Could you please credit $1.80 back to my Raider Account if possible? I don’t really think it is fair that I should have to pay for the 6 color pages I didn’t ask for.
Thank you!
Sarah
Sarah Rowell, MLIS Librarian I MSOE Walter Schroeder Library 414-277-7389 rowell@msoe.edu<mailto:rowell@msoe.edu>

Jenzabar ticket #353723.
The only way to determine when the 1098T report was generated is from the student_yr_report table. This table only shows the values generated by the Student Accounts staff each year.
We aren't able to see when a student actually looks at a report on JICS.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Jenzabar ticket #353723. 

The only way to determine when the 1098T report was generated is from the student_yr_report table. This table only shows the values generated by the Student Accounts staff each year.

We aren't able to see when a student actually looks at a report on JICS.

helpdesk-note.body:
The student most likely generated the 2015 statement before Student Accounts was finished with their 1098T generation process. We think this because the incorrect values listed on his copy of his 2015 report were actually the values from the 2014 calendar year.
The 1098T is available on my.msoe.edu for students to download at any time. But the 1098T's are not completed/updated until the end of January.
Stacey wants to hide the report from students in January until it is completely processed by Student Accounts. That way students are not able to download any old information.
We will just need to uncheck the circled box in JICS 1098T Setup:

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Tracy,
Sorry I keep missing your calls, we are working with Ann this whole week.
Your instinct is correct, if we add the logo to Direct Deposit stub it will show up on Jenzabar Pay Inquiry with the paper clip and on myMSOE. Ann suggested that we actually stop printing physical Direct Deposits stubs altogether and just add the logo so anyone can print it off of myMSOE. This way we don’t have to ever buy that special stock again (I’m sure its pricey). Would that be a good option?
I’m thinking Paycheck stubs are a different case right? Do you usually print all of those?
Jasmine -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hi Jasmine,
That is a great idea. We are actually very low on direct deposit stock and I just sent out for a quote so not having to order any more is a fantastic idea and the timing is perfect. Can we add the logo, and then also add titles to the bottom two lines? I can run over some stock if you need to know what the titles are. Could we also change check# (mid-page) to Number?
Also, it doesn’t appear that the students have access to this link on my.msoe.edu. Can we add this link for them too?
You are correct, we do print all checks, so we would need to keep those as they are now.
Thank you so, so much for working on this!!
Tracy

helpdesk-ticket.subject: How to create a folder on Box.com
helpdesk-ticket.description: I was asked to create a folder on Box, then place info from the O drive into the folder
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: I was asked to create a folder on Box, then place info from the O drive into the folder

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Paula Harrold, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8962
This can be done in a variety of ways. The easiest way is a simply make a new folder in one box sync directory and move the required files into it. Anything that is stored in the box sync folder is automatically stored to the cloud. Another way to make a folder is through the website box.msoe.edu, On the main page simply click new and select folder. From there you can add what ever files you want by ether uploading them to box or dragging them into the new folder in your box sync directory.
Also making copies of files on the O drive is for the most part unnecessary for backup purposes, Those drives are managed by us and have many redundant backups and restore points.
Thanks,
Cameron Wilson Information Technology
Assistant System Admin 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr Barratt, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8993
In response to your request to be aided with the transfer of data off of your work laptop to a private computer. We offer several methods that would allow you to move the data. The first method is to upload all of the data to our Box cloud service. This will allow you to download it on any machine you like. We also offer Onedrive as another cloud storage option. The use of flash drives or external HDD to move larger amounts of data is also something that you might consider. If you have any questions please feel free to reach out to helpdesk on the 3rd floor of the Campus Center or at extension 7288. Have a nice day.
Thanks,
Cameron Wilson Information Technology
Assistant System Admin 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Laptop Screen Stuck in "Projector" Mode
helpdesk-ticket.description: I connected a monitor to my laptop about 2 weeks ago, shut it down and brought it home for the summer. When I shut it down initially, the screen went back to its normal appearance. However, when I turned it back on, the picture is just centered in the middle of my screen, leaving out 1+ inches of available screen on both the left and right. I've been waiting it out to see if it would correct itself, and unfortunately it hasn't. I also am not able to connect to AutoCAD through GlobalProtect. I will be a junior next year so therefore will be getting a new laptop anyway, so if there is no simple solution for these I will deal with it for the next 3 months until I come back to campus and get my new one. Thanks for your help, Joe Fassbender

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi fassbenderj, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8994
If you push the windows key and p at the same time it should rotate through viewing options. You will want to select "Disconnect The Projector" from the four options that are provided. If when rotating through your screen goes back do not worry, this means you are currently on the "Projector Only" Selection. If you push windows + p again it will cycle you through to the next option. Please let us know if this resolves your issue. Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi fassbenderj,
If you right click your desktop background and select "Screen Resolution" it should bring up a window with information about your display. One of the drop down menu's provided should be labeled "Resolution". If you click on it, the drop down will provide a different list of resolutions that your monitor can be set to. One of these should be labeled as the recommended setting. If you select this resolution, and then press "OK". Does this fix your resolution problem?
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8994
 
If you push the windows key and p at the same time it should rotate through viewing options. You will want to select "Disconnect The Projector" from the four options that are provided. If when rotating through your screen goes back do not worry, this means you are currently on the "Projector Only" Selection. If you push windows + p again it will cycle you through to the next option. Please let us know if this resolves your issue.
 
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich
helpdesk@msoe.edu
414-277-7288
On Mon, 13 Jun at 4:08 pm , fassbenderj <fassbenderj@msoe.edu> wrote:
I connected a monitor to my laptop about 2 weeks ago, shut it down and brought it home for the summer.  When I shut it down initially, the screen went back to its normal appearance.  However, when I turned it back on, the picture is just centered in the middle of my screen, leaving out 1+ inches of available screen on both the left and right.  I've been waiting it out to see if it would correct itself, and unfortunately it hasn't.  I also am not able to connect to AutoCAD through GlobalProtect.  I will be a junior next year so therefore will be getting a new laptop anyway, so if there is no simple solution for these I will deal with it for the next 3 months until I come back to campus and get my new one.
 
Thanks for your help,
Joe Fassbender
